Market Cap Formula = Current Market Price per share * Total Number of Outstanding Shares.Market capitalization refers to the total dollar market value of a company\'s outstanding shares of stock.Market cap is used to size up corporations and understand their aggregate market value.

P/E Ratio= Market value per share/Earnings per share\nP/E ratios are used by investors and analysts to determine the relative value of a company\'s shares in an apples-to-apples comparison. It can also be used to compare a company against its own historical records or to compare aggregate markets against one another or over time.​

P/B Ratio= Market Price per Share/Book Value per Share\n​ Companies use the price-to-book ratio (P/B ratio) to compare a firm\'s market capitalization to its book value.A lower P/B ratio could mean the stock is undervalued, and thus more worthy of investing.
Share turnover= the total number of shares traded during some period/the average number of shares outstanding for the same period. The higher the share turnover, the more liquid company shares are.

Contract volume and specifications are necessary parameters for opening a position
It refers to the transaction volume of a trader, that is, the amount of currency to buy/sell.
It refers to the fixed value of the currency pair. The larger the specification, the higher the profit.
What is the point-value of the fluctuation?
It refers to the value of each pip that a foreign exchange currency pair fluctuates by. The larger the specification, the higher the value of one pip that fluctuates.
The unit of measurement to express the change in the value of a symbol.
Forex: the fourth decimal point. Taking EURUSD for example, the difference between 1.08812 and 1.08822 is 1 pip.
XAU/XAG/OIL: the second decimal point. Taking XAUUSD for example, the difference between 1707.61 and 1707.62 is 1 pip; Taking USOIL for example, the difference between 14.565 and 14.575 is 1 pip.
Copper/Nickel: One digit. Taking Copper, for example, the difference between 5166 and 5167 is 1 pip.
BTC/LTC/ETH：the second decimal point. Taking BTCUSD for example, the difference between 7740.17 and 7740.18 is 1 pip.
XRP: the fifth decimal point. The difference between 0.20938 and 0.20939 is 1 pip.

“Pending order” means that users set a target price (limit price) in advance, then positions will be opened automatically at the target price or the next best available market price.
Why do we need to set“deviation”?

It takes little time to process pending orders. Sometimes, the market fluctuates faster than the system and market price diverges from the target price, hence the position may open at the next best available market price.

In order to resolve the above issues, our system allows a deviation between the final market price and the limit price.The deviation is set by the user. In order to open positions successfully, users are suggested to set the deviation slightly wider. For example, if the target price of gold is 1352.25 , you set the “10 pips ”as deviations, then the position can be opened at the price of 1352.25-1352.35 according to the market condition.

as defined by the US Internal Revenue Service (IRS) includes any:
- A U.S. citizen or resident (including dual citizenship)
- A U.S. alien (resident for tax purposes)
- A US partnership
- A US corporation
- Owns any estate other than a foreign estate
- Member of a trust whereby: a. A court within the U.S. is able to exercise primary supervision over the administration of the trust b. One or more U.S. citizens have the authority to control all substantial decisions of the trust
- Any other person that is not a foreign person
